/* ==== picker-base.js ==== */
/* ==========================================================================
   Aura — picker-base: shared scaffolding for the anchored-popup pickers.

   The datepicker (role=dialog grid) and timepicker (role=listbox columns) are
   different keyboard models but share the SAME picker shell shape: a canonical
   value mirrored to hidden input(s), an optional dual-endpoint RANGE value
   ("start/end"), locale-driven display, and an anchored popup placed via
   Aura.overlay.placeAtAnchor with flip/clamp + a revert-on-Escape snapshot.

   This module factors that duplicated scaffolding out of the two pickers
   (#338, #323) into pure, independently-testable units under Aura.pickers:

     • range value helpers — splitRange / orderPair (the "start/end" model both
       pickers re-implemented identically);
     • localeCycle — resolve the locale's default 12/24 hour cycle (the
       timepicker's locale-cycling concern, lifted to a shared, testable unit);
     • makeRevertOverlay — the anchored-overlay-with-revert lifecycle skeleton
       (detach to <body>, place, animate exit, restore home) that wraps the
       shared Aura.overlay geometry but keeps each picker's own commit/revert
       and keyboard model on top.

   The keyboard models stay in their own files (the grid vs. listbox engines are
   genuinely different); only the lifecycle/overlay/value scaffolding is shared.

   Load order: core.js → element-base.js → overlay.js → picker-base.js → pickers.
   ========================================================================== */
